b'"No matter how you look at it, we have blood on our hands. Right now, we have all the technology we need to leave fossil fuels in the past. We have a moral obligation to use it."'
b'\xe2\x80\x9cIt\xe2\x80\x99s not whether we need to move forward, it\xe2\x80\x99s how quickly we move forward.\xe2\x80\x9d -@EPAMichaelRegan'
b'\xe2\x80\x9cEveryone deserves clean air, clean water, and to be safe from environmental hazard and harm.\xe2\x80\x9d -@EPAMichaelRegan'
b'\xe2\x80\x9cEnvironmental justice is the fair and equal regulation of pollution for every single person in the United States and around the world.\xe2\x80\x9d -@EPAMichaelRegan'
b'\xe2\x80\x9cI may be the EPA Administrator, but my 8 year old is the head environmentalist in my home.\xe2\x80\x9d -@EPAMichaelRegan'
b'\xe2\x80\x9cI am so optimistic. Every major movement in the United States has been led by young people and this is going to be no different.\xe2\x80\x9d -@EPAMichaelRegan'
b'\xe2\x80\x9cCollectively all of us all across the world can solve this problem.\xe2\x80\x9d @EPAMichaelRegan'
b'\xe2\x80\x9cAll of us for the first time in history, are rowing in the same direction.\xe2\x80\x9d -@EPAMichaelRegan'
b'"We don\xe2\x80\x99t need movie magic. We have all of the tools to save the world. We can be the heroes we have been waiting for. We can build the future."'
b'"We must do whatever it takes to eliminate our addiction to fossil fuels. We must be part of the solution, not part of the problem."'
b'"We owe it to the millions of Ellas struggling to breathe around the world. We owe it to the Ukrainian children growing up in bomb shelters. We owe it to ourselves."'
b'"Right now, we have all the technology we need to leave fossil fuels in the past. We have a moral obligation to use it."'
b'"I want to thank Rosamund for standing up and showing all of us that we can\xe2\x80\x99t keep lying. We have to tell the truth."'
b'"Normally her death certificate would have said asthma. But Rosamund fought for the truth to save other children. Ella became the first person whose official cause of death was pollution."'
b'"The last 2 years of her life, Ella was hospitalized 30 times for asthma attacks. And one terrible day, the doctors couldn\xe2\x80\x99t save her."'
b'"Their family lived less than a hundred feet from South Circular Road, one of the busiest roads in London, with thousands of cars and buses and extremely high levels of pollution."'
b'My friend Rosamund is here today. She lost her beautiful 9 year old daughter, Ella, to pollution.'
b'"7 million people were killed by pollution last year. SEVEN MILLION! That\xe2\x80\x99s not just a number."'
b'"You have said it yourselves: This isn\xe2\x80\x99t just climate change. This is a climate emergency.\nI agree with you. This is an emergency."'
b'Everywhere you look the clean energy revolution is firing on all cylinders, or in this case, batteries.'
b'\xe2\x80\x9c15 years ago the only option was a weird looking car that could barely get around town, and no one could fit in it. Now, electric cars are beautiful!\xe2\x80\x9d'
b'\xe2\x80\x9cSince 2015, electric vehicle sales have increased by 50% every year.\xe2\x80\x9d'
b'\xe2\x80\x9cTechnology makes the impossible possible.\xe2\x80\x9d'
